subSubSection.paragraph:
Dryocosmus hearni

: the head and mesosoma of females and males are orange-yellow (Figs 
64-69
, 
72-73
), the metasoma is dark brown. The notaulus posterior region width / anterior region width = 5 (Fig. 
73
); posterior height of subaxillular bar / height of metanotal trough = 0.25 (Fig. 
72
); the central propodeal area is with a transverse carina in dorsal 1/3rd (Fig. 
74
).

The notaulus posterior region width / anterior region width = 1 (Fig. 
181
), posterior height of subaxillular bar / height of metanotal trough>1; the central propodeal area without a transverse carina in dorsal 1/3rd (Fig. 
179
).

Gall (Fig. 
76
): Galls are integrated leaf swellings, usually located at the base of leaves, and are concolorous with the leaves. The galls are 22.4-24.3 mm long, 18.2-19.0 mm wide (n=3).
